<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>by inches • inch by inch</xh5><p> <i>by inches—</i>1. very gradually or slowly: The ship was sinking <u>by inches</u>; she might remain above water an hour or more. 2. <i>miss </i>by a very small margin: We scrambled to get out of the way, the car missing us <u>by inches</u>.</p><p><i>inch by inch—</i>1. by small degrees or stages: When life falls apart, we are forced to rebuild it <u>inch by inch</u>. 2. <i>scrutinize smth. </i>closely; <i>examine smth. </i>very carefully: I have examined that cloth <u>inch by inch</u>; there is not a flaw in it.</p> </entry>
